🟢 Method 3 (Clean method – recommended for learning)
Start properly from GitHub:
git clone https://github.com/Dhanyashriee/myproject.git
cd myproject

git checkout -b feature/hello
# create file again
git add .
git commit -m "feat: add hello.txt"
git push origin feature/hello
✔ This ensures same history
________________________________________
🔍 What you did RIGHT (important)
From your terminal:
✔ git add ✅
✔ git commit ✅
✔ git push ✅
✔ branch created ✅
👉 So your understanding is correct — just a history mismatch issue.
________________________________________
🧠 Simple understanding
Think like this:
•	GitHub main = 📘 Book 1 
•	Your branch = 📕 Book 2 
Git says:
👉 “These books are unrelated”
So you must combine them first
________________________________________
🚀 What you should do now (simple steps)
👉 Do this:
git pull origin main --allow-unrelated-histories
Then go to GitHub → refresh → create PR
